<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc075f4f3-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s18998"><num value="18998">§ 18998.</num><heading> Mandatory cost-sharing</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idc075f4f4-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s18998/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Waiver</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The cost-sharing requirements under section 1862<i>o</i>-14(c) of this title for the Major Research Instrumentation Program and under section 1862n-1a(i) of this title for teaching fellowships administered within the Robert Noyce Teacher Scholarship Program are waived for a period of 5 years following <date date="2022-08-09">August 9, 2022</date>.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="idc075f4f5-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s18998/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Assessment</heading><chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Not later than 5 years following <date date="2022-08-09">August 9, 2022</date>, the Director shall submit to Congress an assessment, that includes feedback from the research community, of the impacts of the waivers provided under subsection (a), including—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idc075f4f6-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s18998/b/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> programmatic and scientific goals;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idc075f4f7-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s18998/b/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> institutional commitment and stewardship of Federal resources;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idc075f4f8-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s18998/b/3"><num value="3">(3)</num><content> institutional strategic planning and administrative burden;</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idc075f4f9-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s18998/b/4"><num value="4">(4)</num><content> equity among recipient institutions; and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idc075f4fa-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s18998/b/5"><num value="5">(5)</num><content> recommendations for or against extending or making permanent such waivers.</content>
</paragraph>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="idc075f4fb-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/117/167/dB/tIII/s10320">Pub. L. 117–167, div. B, title III, § 10320</ref>, <date date="2022-08-09">Aug. 9, 2022</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/136/1536">136 Stat. 1536</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
